propClasses: Override or extend the styles applied to the component.
propCollapseIcon: The icon used to collapse the node.
propContentComponent: The component used for the content node.
propEndIcon: The icon displayed next to a end node.
propExpandIcon: The icon used to expand the node.
propIcon: The icon to display next to the tree node's label.
propOnFocus:
This prop isn't supported.
Use the `onNodeFocus` callback on the tree if you need to monitor a node's focus.
propTransitionComponent:
The component used for the transition.
[Follow this guide](/components/transitions/#transitioncomponent-prop) to learn more about the requirements for this component.
propTransitionProps:
Props applied to the transition element.
By default, the element is based on this [`Transition`](http://reactcommunity.org/react-transition-group/transition) component.
stylesRoot: Styles applied to the root element.
stylesContent: Styles applied to the content element.
stylesExpanded: Pseudo-class applied to the content element when expanded.
stylesSelected: Pseudo-class applied to the content element when selected.
stylesFocused: Pseudo-class applied to the content element when focused.
stylesDisabled: Pseudo-class applied to the element when disabled.
stylesIconContainer: Styles applied to the tree node icon.
stylesLabel: Styles applied to the label element.
